            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This one bit me today. Not only is the `shy` character impossible to see or list, but commands like `f<space>` also produce extraneous results by finding ghost spaces.\r\n\r\nThe behavior to the observer was similar to having a broken terminal. I tried exiting neovim and running reset, but nothing changed. The only way forward was selecting the whole text and running `!xxd` on it.",
