            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I partially solved the underlying issue of text artifacts and visibility by adding soft‑hyphens as concealed characters:\n\n```lua\n--- Conceals soft hyphens with a hyphen.\n---\n--- Kitty, Neovim and soft hyphens don’t mix. Soft hyphens in things like HTML code text shifting\n--- artifacts: https://github.com/kovidgoyal/kitty/issues/4094.\n---\n--- This function helps avoid that by concealing soft hyphens. It’s good to couple it with\n--- concealcursor = \"n\" to ensure that the concealment stays in normal mode.\nfunction M.conceal_soft_hyphens()\n\tvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"BufWinEnter\" }, {\n\t\tpattern = \"*\",\n\t\tcallback = function(_)\n\t\t\tvim.fn.matchadd(\"Conceal\", [[\\%u00ad]], 10, -1, { conceal = \"-\" })\n\t\tend,\n\t\tdesc = \"Conceal soft hyphens\",\n\t})\nend\n```\n\nThis is how it looks (requires `conceallevel` to be set to 2):\n\n<img width=\"708\" height=\"70\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0ad42432-b024-402b-84b9-94a34b9533c1\" />\n\n<img width=\"372\" height=\"107\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ac2aea7d-834d-4a5e-a76b-9129220773d8\" />\n\nI agree that it would still be preferable to use the `list` functionality for shys, because we shouldn’t rely on `conceallevel=2` for this.",
